{"word":"G5342 - φέρω - phérō - fer'-o - Be","slug":"G5342","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φέρω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>phérō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>fer'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Be"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C6;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03C9; - phero&#x0304;&#x0304;</b> - <i>fer'-o</i><p/>A primary verb (for which other and apparently not cognate ones are used in certain tenses only; namely <b>&#x03BF;&#x03B9;&#x0313;&#x0301;&#x03C9;</b> <b>oio&#x0304;&#x0304;&#x0304;</b> and <b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03BD;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03B3;&#x03BA;&#x03C9;</b> <b>enegko&#x0304;&#x0304;</b> to &ldquo;bear&rdquo; or <i>carry</i> (in a very wide application, literally and figuratively: - be, bear, bring (forth), carry, come, + let her drive, be driven, endure, go on, lay, lead, move, reach, rushing, uphold."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1308\">G1308</a>, <a href=\"#/G1313\">G1313</a>, <a href=\"#/G2018\">G2018</a>, <a href=\"#/G399\">G399</a>, <a href=\"#/G4374\">G4374</a>, <a href=\"#/G4376\">G4376</a>, <a href=\"#/G4851\">G4851</a>, <a href=\"#/G5409\">G5409</a>, <a href=\"#/G5411\">G5411</a>, <a href=\"#/G5412\">G5412</a>, <a href=\"#/G5413\">G5413</a>, <a href=\"#/G5414\">G5414</a>"}]}